{"cursor":"16556","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox writer \n| name = Jia Pingwa è´¾å¹³å¹ image = image_size = alt = caption = pseudonym = Jia\n| Pingwa birth_name = Jia Pingwa (è´¾å¹³å¨) birth_date = birth_place = Shangluo,\n| Shaanxi, China death_date =  death_place = resting_place = occupation\n| = Writer language = Chinese nationality = Chinese ethnicity = citizenship =\n| education = Graduated - Northwest University School of Arts (1975) alma_mater\n| = period = 1972 â present genre = subject = movement = notableworks =\n| [[Deserted City]],  [[My Little Peach Tree]] spouse = Han Junfang (é©ä¿è³)\n|  (1979.1.22-1992.11.26)  Guo Mei (é­æ¢)  (1996.12.12â present)\n| partner = children = Jia Qianqian (è´¾æµæµ)  Jia Ruo (è´¾è¥) relatives =\n| influences = influenced = awards = signature = signature_alt = website =\n| portaldisp =\n}}\n\n' Jia Pingwa' (; born 21 February 1952), formerly known as Jia Pingwa (), is a\nChinese novelist and short story writer. He was born in Dihua Town, Danfeng,\nShangluo, Shaanxi, graduated from Northwest University School of Arts in\n1975, began to publish works in 1972. His novels includes \"Shang\nState\", \"White Night\", and the autobiographical \"I am a Farmer\". His 1993 novel,\nDeserted City was banned for its explicit sexual content by the State Publishing\nAdministration. The novel was re-released 17 years later. His most\nfamous novel is Shaanxi Opera, which won the Mao Dun Literature Prize.\n\nHe is the Chairman of the Writers' Association of Shaanxi Province,\nand a member of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political\nConsultative Conference and Xi'an People's Congress. Currently he\nalso is a member of the Presidium of the Chinese Writers'\nAssociation, Xi'an Literary Federation President, Xi'an Writers'\nAssociation Honorary Chairman, Dean of the College of Arts of Xi'an\nUniversity of Architecture and Technology, the editor-in-chief of\n\"Essay\" (Mei Wen),  In-school writer of the Ocean University of\nChina.\n\nHe has been cited as the China's third most popular writer in a biennial poll\nconducted by the Chinese Publishing Science Research Center in 2006.\n","linknr":228,"url":"Jia_Pingwa","recorded":1375066138,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Jia_Pingwa&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Jia_Pingwa&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Chinese_name","/wiki/Chinese_surname","/w/index.php?title=Jia_(surname)&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Shangluo","/wiki/Shaanxi","/wiki/China","/wiki/Chinese_language","/wiki/China","/wiki/Northwest_University_(China)","/w/index.php?title=Deserted_City&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=My_Little_Peach_Tree&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters","/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters","/wiki/Pinyin","/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters","/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters","/wiki/Pinyin","/wiki/China","/wiki/Danfeng_County","/wiki/Shangluo","/wiki/Shaanxi","/wiki/Northwest_University_(China)","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Mao_Dun_Literature_Prize","#cite_note-maodun-3","#cite_note-4","/wiki/National_Committee_of_the_Chinese_People%27s_Political_Consultative_Conference","#cite_note-5",